# Understand-Anything generates intermediate per-agent artifacts here while the
# plugin assembles the final knowledge graph. Those intermediates (and any
# future scratch the upstream tool decides to write) are not meant to be
# committed. We use an ignore-everything pattern with an explicit allow-list
# so new scratch files default to ignored, mirroring `.gitnexus/.gitignore`.
*

# Allow this file itself + the curated/canonical artifacts:
#   .gitignore              — this file
#   README.md               — directory documentation
#   knowledge-graph.json    — the assembled multi-agent graph
#   onboarding.md           — /understand-onboard output
#   tours/                  — /understand-dashboard guided tours
!.gitignore
!README.md
!knowledge-graph.json
!onboarding.md
!tours/
